  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-09-16",
    "date": "2003-12-03T16:02:30Z",
    "text": "David Shick Honesty in Campus Justice Act - Amends the General Education Provisions Act to require an institution of post-secondary education to disclose to the alleged victim of any crime of violence or a non-forcible sex offense (or to a deceased victim's next of kin) the final results of any disciplinary proceeding conducted by such institution against a student who is the alleged perpetrator. (Current law states that such disclosure is not prohibited.)"
